result.execSummary:
The defendant Cyle Ray Jones was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Drive or Operate Vehicle w/o Consent, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(3).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

3:39 PM Attorney Fredric B. Anderson in court for Cyle Ray Jones.  Attorney Mark Adam Fruehauf in court for State of Wisconsin. Notes that defendant does not appear by stipulation. The restitution amount is not contested. State reviews breakdown of restitution. State notes that vehicle was impounded in Duluth and defendant's vehicle was scrapped, thus defendant needed to buy a new vehicle. State asks for impound fee and storage fees in the amount of $1267.65, although victim would like restitution in the amount of a new vehicle. Victims makes statement regarding what happened to the vehicle, vehicle was recently bought and was not titled in Victim's name. Attorney Anderson notes that defendant should not have to pay for new vehicle but does not contest the amount given by the State. Court orders restitution on the amount of $1,267.65. Court informs victim that they can file a civil suit if they feel that they are entitled to more, but the criminal case will only allow for certain restitution amounts to be granted.

9:07 AM Defendant Cyle Ray Jones in court, in custody.  Attorney Fredric B. Anderson in court for Cyle Ray Jones.  Attorney Mark Adam Fruehauf in court for State of Wisconsin. State recites agreement that defendant to plead to Count 1. Count 2 to be dismissed but read in. For Count 1, serve 110 days jail with credit for 110 days, pay mandatory court costs and restitution order but contested so set a hearing to be converted to a civil judgment. State has complied with Victim's Rights. Defendant pleads no contest. Attorney Anderson stipulates to a factual basis. Court accepts the Defendant's plea and finds that the Defendant's plea has been freely, voluntarily and intelligently made. The Defendant understands all the rights he is waiving by his plea. The Defendant is found guilty and Judgment of Conviction is entered.

Court imposes for Count 1, serve 110 days jail with credit for 110 days-time served and pay mandatory court costs. Restitution Hearing set.
